Engineer Joe Igbokwe, the special adviser to the governor of Lagos State on drainage and water resources was on his Facebook account this evening to quote a statement made by Abdulmumin Jibrin concerning Bola Tinubu.
In the shared statement, Jibrin revealed that he was shocked when he discovered that Bola Tinubu has huge shares in Apple corporation, one of the most valuable technology companies in the world and he also discovered that Tinubu owns a large amount of shares in Manchester United, one of the biggest football clubs in the world, Jibrin noted that he made this discovery while he was watching football with Tinubu recently.
Abdulmumin Jibrin then went further to let people know that Tinubu has been funding pro democracy groups with his investments since the 90s and nobody has come out to argue about that, Jibrin then wondered why people didn’t ask Tinubu were he got his money from when he was funding the fight for democracy in Nigeria.
Some of Tinubu’s sources of income are beginning to unfold, for those asking or wandering how Tinubu got so much money, those that are close to him are already revealing his income sources little by little, with time all other questions will be addressed.
